Police in Maake outside Tzaneen Limpopo have on Wednesday launched a manhunt for the suspects who burnt a local Primary School.&#8220;It is alleged that a mysterious fire burnt two classrooms and two mobile classrooms at Shiluvane Primary School on Monday.&#8220;The principal was alerted by the school&#8217;s security guard. Unfortunately upon arrival, the fire had already destroyed the classrooms&#8221;, said police spokesperson, Lt Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe.However there were no injuries or fatalities.The cause of the fire is still unknown but the police are relying on results from the Forensic investigations.Ngoepe encouraged anyone with information to come forward as no arrests have yet been made.TNA Reporter